  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reserve for emergency to respond to the relocation of IDPs from gathering sites to Krindig camps in West Darfur</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to enable people displaced by conflicts in Krinding camp access safe water and improve their hygiene and sanitation. The project will construct 20 latrines in schools, rehabilitate 20 latrines in schools, distribute hygiene items in 10 schools and also distribute hygiene kits to 494 households, provide500 cartons of soap to households and schools and provide 20 hand washing facilities to improve hand hygiene in schools.  The project will also create awareness in the targeted community on hygiene and sanitation and distribute IEC materials and conduct outreaches in the IDP camps and in schools. To guarantee access to clean and safe water, the project will drill 10 hand pumps and rehabilitate another 20 hand pumps. The project will also support water tracking in Krindig IDP for those in locations without water sources.</narrative>
  </description>
